/***************************************************************************/
/*                                                                         */
/* User synonyms.  These are useful for overriding internal editor         */
/* functions.  The available keywords are:                                 */
/*                                                                         */
/*   BEEP        - executed when the editor issues an alarm, i.e. when a   */
/*                 Locate command wraps around the file, or when error     */
/*                 parsing is being performed through the /Q edit switch   */
/*   CHANGE      - executed whenever a change command is issued from the   */
/*                 command line, i.e. not from a macro                     */
/*   EDIT        - executed when a file is about to be added to the editor */
/*   ERROR_PARSE - executed when error information is to be added to a     */
/*                 file                                                    */
/*   EXIT        - executed when the editor is terminating, i.e. after the */
/*                 last file has been quit                                 */
/*   LOAD        - executed when a file has just been added to the editor  */
/*   LOCATE      - executed whenever a locate/find command is issued from  */
/*                 the command line, i.e. not from a macro                 */
/*   NEWFILE     - executed when a new file has just been added to the     */
/*                 editor                                                  */
/*   QUIT        - executed when a file is being removed from the editor   */
/*   SAVE        - executed when a file is to be saved to disk             */
/*   STARTUP     - executed when the editor is starting                    */
/*                                                                         */
/* The HOSTEDIT.X synonym is available from X2 PROCS on IBMPC.  To install */
/* it, copy and download it to a directory on your PATH, copy the relevant */
/* synonym lines to your XPROFILE.ADD, and uncomment them by deleting the  */
/* leading asterisks.                                                      */
/*                                                                         */
/***************************************************************************/

* synonym beep        = macro whatever
* synonym change      = macro whatever
* synonym edit        = macro hostedit edit
* synonym error_parse = macro whatever
* synonym exit        = macro whatever
* synonym load        = macro whatever
* synonym locate      = macro whatever
* synonym newfile     = macro whatever
* synonym quit        = macro whatever
* synonym save        = macro hostedit save
* synonym startup     = macro whatever


